 6.2  Gold and Base Metal Exploration 
 Prior gold and base metal exploration has primarily focused on the follow up of the stream 
 sediment  sampling.    The  gold  anomalism  could  be  sourced  from  a  number  of  different 
 styles of mineralisation.  In summary these are:   
 Alluvial  placer  gold  eroding  from  clastics  and  sandstones  at  the  base  of  the 
 Quartz veins with sulphide mineralisation associated with fold hinges. 
 Epithermal style veining previously identified at the Whaleback prospect to the south 
 Veining or ironstone hosted mineralisation associated with northeast faults and east-
 northeast faults parallel to the Homestead Fault. This style of mineralization appears 
 to be related to basin wide tectonics of the Capricorn orogeny.  
 No exploration studies were undertaken in the past year for gold or base metals.  
 EXPLORATION  STUDIES  IN  THE  REPORTING  PERIOD  –  7  JULY  2006  TO  6

 primary focus being on assessing the iron ore prospectivity of the project area. A review of 
 past  exploration  studies  was  completed  along  with  Landsat,  geophysical  and  geological 
 interpretation  studies.  In  April  2007  a  reconnaissance  field  trip  of  the  project  area  was 
 undertaken where rock chip sampling was completed.
